programme.title: Fox News Sunday With Chris Wallace
programme.desc: Donald Trump's campaign manager Corey Lewandowski on the race for the White House; Sen. James Lankford (R-Okla.) and Rep. Adam Schiff (D-Cal.) on Hillary Clinton's e-mails. Also: an interview with Bugles Across America founder Tom Day. Panelists include political analyst Brit Hume, Susan Page (USA Today), columnist George Will and Ron Fournier (National Journal)(n)

programme.title: MediaBuzz
programme.desc: Topics: Hillary Clinton's e-mails; Donald Trump's comments about Bill Clinton's past with women; Katie Couric's documentary "Under the Gun." Also: an interview with Trump campaign spokesperson Katrina Pierson. Guests include Susan Ferrechio (Washington Examiner), Democratic strategist Penny Lee, Republican strategist Lisa Boothe and Farhad Manjoo (New York Times)(n)

programme.title: Horizon
programme.desc: BBC weatherman Peter Gibbs makes an emotional return to the British Antarctic Survey's Halley Research Station, where he lived and worked in the early 1980s. During that period, the station was key to the discovery of the Ozone Hole, and today it is making vital findings about how people's lives are vulnerable to the Sun's activities, as well as studying interplanetary travel and the threat of man-man climate change. In addition to returning to the place he once called home, Peter is on a rescue mission, since the station is under threat of being cast adrift on a huge iceberg.(n)
